{"id":14880778,"mediaExerciseId":"8099582c-0f8a-41d7-abb6-b11023aff1f9","exerciseName":"2","chapterName":"3","chapterTitle":"Working with Financial Statements","groupId":null,"groupTitle":null,"isPremium":true,"sectionName":"3.2","sectionTitle":"Standardized Financial Statements","pageNumber":57,"solutions":[{"id":5904022,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"In this problem, we are required to determine why is it necessary to standardize financial statements and the two types of standardized statements.","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"Before we begin, let us first define financial statements.\n\n**Financial statements** are formal records which show the financial activities and performance of a company. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"a. It is often necessary to standardize financial statements because it is useful for comparison purposes for an accounting year as well as for comparison of companies of different sizes within the same industry.","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/325f541cfbdb54ec275600bec6151f38/1ba5aa6c0005a6b07d62496b705f9c18/lateximg_large.png","width":1020},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/325f541cfbdb54ec275600bec6151f38/1ba5aa6c0005a6b07d62496b705f9c18/lateximg.png","width":510}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3},{"columns":[{"text":"b. The two types of standardized statements are:\n- Common Size Statements\n- Common Base Year Financial Statements","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":61,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/325f541cfbdb54ec275600bec6151f38/469455d4c3cbb9a725032b3d82f6224a/lateximg_large.png","width":732},"regular":{"height":32,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/325f541cfbdb54ec275600bec6151f38/469455d4c3cbb9a725032b3d82f6224a/lateximg.png","width":366}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":4},{"columns":[{"text":"**Common Size Statements**, also known as vertical analysis, express line items as a percentage of one common figure. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":103,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/325f541cfbdb54ec275600bec6151f38/925aca3a7d616b3055081eb6202d778c/lateximg_large.png","width":996},"regular":{"height":53,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/325f541cfbdb54ec275600bec6151f38/925aca3a7d616b3055081eb6202d778c/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":5},{"columns":[{"text":"**Common Base Year Financial Statements** show the growth rate of an account by choosing a base year and express each line item respective to the base amount. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":70,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/325f541cfbdb54ec275600bec6151f38/ecc2b12ffd7a9795669953f02e79dac6/lateximg_large.png","width":1031},"regular":{"height":35,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/18/325f541cfbdb54ec275600bec6151f38/ecc2b12ffd7a9795669953f02e79dac6/lateximg.png","width":515}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":6}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"18fe453a-5d18-4ab8-b7d8-b2e7bc5e7134","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":6},{"id":5950509,"modifiedOn":"2021-01-01T00:00:00.000000","steps":[{"columns":[{"text":"For this exercise, we are tasked to determine the need to standardized financial statements and identify the different types of it. ","images":{"latex":{"large":{"height":66,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/28/d65b2050bde8e8028819f771bf145c6c/0688808864d4f5900226729e6bbff5b8/lateximg_large.png","width":995},"regular":{"height":34,"srcUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/21/12/28/d65b2050bde8e8028819f771bf145c6c/0688808864d4f5900226729e6bbff5b8/lateximg.png","width":498}},"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":true}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":1},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement 1a\nFinancial statements are often standardized for the purpose of directly comparing different entities of different sizes. This is to avoid any problems and to easily compare each other. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":2},{"columns":[{"text":"## Requirement 1b\nThe two types of standardized financial statements are as follows. \n1. Common-size statements- this is formed by dividing each element of the financial statement by the total asset or the total sales. Each item is presented as a percentage of each total. \n2. Common-base year statement- Also called trend analysis. It is formed by dividing each item in the financial statement by its relative base amount from the chosen base year. ","images":{"latex":null,"additional":null},"hasInvalidKatex":false,"isTextOnly":false}],"isResult":false,"stepNumber":3}],"rating":5,"solutionUuid":"cbf36bba-7d30-4488-b3b1-274ce8b595fe","editorVersion":2,"answeredOn":null,"ratingCount":null,"solutionOrder":null,"totalSteps":3}],"textbook":{"authors":"Bradford D. Jordan, Randolph W. Westerfield, Stephen A. Ross","imageUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/textbook_covers/tmpm0p82b7h","imageThumbnailUrl":"https://d2nchlq0f2u6vy.cloudfront.net/cache/d1/d3/d1d34d106dd29dd2e71be582412ef59d.jpg","id":34320,"isbn":"9781259918957","isPremium":true,"title":"Fundamentals of Corporate Finance","edition":"12th Edition","verifiedSolutionCount":1217,"shouldBeIndexableForSeo":true,"modified":1665448474394,"active":true,"publisher":"McGraw-Hill Education","mainTextbookIsbn":null,"subjects":{"level1":["Social Science"],"level2":["Economics"],"level3":["Finance"]}},"nextExercises":[{"id":14880779,"exerciseName":"3","page":69,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"bb52f27f-02bd-436e-9bab-5c384e84d61c","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-3-exercises-3-bb52f27f-02bd-436e-9bab-5c384e84d61c"}],"previousExercises":[{"id":14880777,"exerciseName":"1","page":54,"hasSolution":true,"mediaExerciseId":"1d935d33-643b-40d7-a2b0-df6f7be49e25","_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-3-exercises-1-1d935d33-643b-40d7-a2b0-df6f7be49e25"}],"_webUrl":"https://quizlet.com/explanations/textbook-solutions/fundamentals-of-corporate-finance-12th-edition-9781259918957/chapter-3-exercises-2-8099582c-0f8a-41d7-abb6-b11023aff1f9"}